==English==
===Etymology===
From {{It.}} '''[[papa]]''', familiar form from {{L.}} '''[[pater]]''', ''[[father]]'', ultimately from [[Proto-Indo-European]]
{{wikipedia}}
===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: /pōp/
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /pəʊp/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /p@Up/

===Noun===
'''pope''', plural '''[[popes]]'''

# the bishop of Rome; the head of the [[Roman Catholic]] church.
[[Category:Christianity]]
# similar head of another church or religious group.  For example, the [[Patriarch]] of Alexandria is called "Pope Shenouda".

